{"lemma": "عَلِيٌّ", "slug": "عَلِيٌّ", "root": "ع.ل.#", "root_slug": "ع-ل-_", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ل-_", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "عَلِيّ", "root": "علو", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 11}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 6, "pos_tags": ["adj", "name", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 7}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n30138", "n30405", "n30406", "n30407", "n30408", "n30422", "n30423", "n30428"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "Ali", "fa": "علی", "ur": "علی", "tr": "Ali", "id": "Ali", "bn": "আলি", "es": "Ali", "fr": "Ali", "de": "Ali", "ru": "Али", "zh": "阿里"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be exalted, high", "tags": ["intransitive"], "examples": [{"text": "عَلِيَ ٱلْقَمَرُ فِي سَمَاءِ ٱللَّيْلِ", "english": "The moon rose up in the night sky."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to excel, to stand out", "tags": ["intransitive"], "examples": [{"text": "عَلِيَ فِي ٱلْمَجْدِ وَٱلْمَكَارِمِ"}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "high, tall"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "exalted, lofty, excellent"}, {"pos": "name", "gloss": "a male given name, Ali"}, {"pos": "name", "gloss": "ʿAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib, the son-in-law of the Islamic prophet Muhammad through Ali's marriage to the Islamic prophet's daughter, Fāṭimah al-Zahrāʾ, recognized as the Islamic prophet's fourth rightly-guided successor in most of Sunni Islam and as the Islamic prophet's first legitimate successor in Shia Islam"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of عَلَى (ʕalā) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Ultimately from Proto-Semitic *ʕall-, *ʕaly- (“to be high; exalted”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *ʕal-, *ʕVl(ay)- (“to be high, tall; to rise, ascend”).\nCognate with Hebrew עָלָה (ʿalá, “to ascend, rise, grow, develop”), Hebrew עלי (ʿeli, “ascent”) and thereby Eli.\n\nFrom the root ع ل و (ʕ l w) or ع ل ي (ʕ l y)."}, "ipa": ["/ʕa.li.ja/", "/ʕa.lijj/", "/ʕalj/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n30138", "headword_ar": "عُِلِّىٌّ", "root": "El", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see the next paragraph, in three places."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30405", "headword_ar": "عَلْىٌ", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaloyaA='u", "text_ar": "عَلْيَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30406", "headword_ar": "عِلْىٌ", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaliY~N", "text_ar": "عَلِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30407", "headword_ar": "عَلَى", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "is a particle and a noun (Mbr, S, Mughnee, K) and a verb; (Mbr, S;) though some assert that it is only a noun, and ascribe this assertion to Sb: (Mughnee:) its alif, (Sb, S, Msb,) [which, when it has no affix, is written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and] which is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Sb, S,) [like that of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY", "text_ar": "اـِلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.,] is changed into [what is properly]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when it has a pronominal affix, (Sb, S, Msb,) as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayoka", "text_ar": "عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Sb, S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) but some of the Arabs [in this case] leave it unchanged, as in the saying of a rájiz,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "TaAruwA EalaAhun~a faTiro EalaAhaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They fled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "have fled, upon them,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(referring to camels,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and flee thou upon her"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; this, it is said, being of the dial. of Belhárith Ibn-Kaab. (Sb, S.) ―         -b2-  As a particle, it has nine [or more than nine] meanings. (Mughnee.) As such, (Mughnee,) or, accord. to Sb, as a noun, (K,) it denotes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAisotiEolaA='", "text_ar": "الاِسْتِعْلَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. superiority] (Msb, Es-Subkee, Mughnee, K, TA) properly thus termed, (Msb,) such as is perceptible by sense; (Es-Subkee, TA;) either with respect to what is signified by the noun governed by it, and this is generally the case, (Mughnee,) as in the saying [in the Kur xxiii. 22 and xl. 80],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waEalayohaA waEalaY A@lofuloki tuHomaluwna", "text_ar": "وَعَلَيْهَا وَعَلَى ا@لْفُلْكِ تُحْمَلُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And upon them"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(referring to camels)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and upon the ship,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ships, ye are carried"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee, K;) or with respect to what is near thereto, as in the saying [in the Kur xx. 10],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^awo A^ajidu", "text_ar": "اَوْ اَجِدُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A@ln~aAri hudFY", "text_ar": "عَلَى ا@لنَّارِ هُدًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Or I shall find near upon the fire,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the fire, a right direction"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee:) and using it to denote"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAstElA='", "text_ar": "الاستعلا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "properly thus termed, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kunotu EalaY Als~aToHi", "text_ar": "كُنْتُ عَلَى السَّطْحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I was"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2145}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon the flat house-top"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Msb:) [in like manner also,] as denoting"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAstElA='", "text_ar": "الاستعلا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that is perceptible by sense, it occurs in the saying [in the Kur lv. 26],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~u mano EalayohaA faAnK", "text_ar": "كُلُّ مَنْ عَلَيْهَا فَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Every one that is upon it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(referring to the earth)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is transitory"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Es-Subkee, TA:) and you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY zayodK vawobN", "text_ar": "عَلَى زَيْدٍ ثَوْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Upon Zeyd is,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was, a garment"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being here a particle; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaA zayodFA vawobN", "text_ar": "عَلَا زَيْدًا ثَوْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A garment was upon Zeyd,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaA", "text_ar": "عَلَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being here a verb. (Mbr, S.) And it denotes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAstElA='", "text_ar": "الاستعلا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", likewise, tropically thus termed, (Msb, TA,) such as is ideal, or perceived by the intel-lect; (Msb, Es-Subkee, Mughnee, TA;) as in the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodN Ealayohi dayonN", "text_ar": "زَيْدٌ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Zeyd, a debt is lying upon him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "incumbent on him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he owes a debt,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lifulaAnK", "text_ar": "لِفُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to such a one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], that which is ideal being thus likened to that which is corporeal; (Msb;) and in the phrases"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalayonaA A^amorN", "text_ar": "عَلَيْنَا اَمْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalayonaA maAlN", "text_ar": "عَلَيْنَا مَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a command, lies,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rests, upon us,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is incumbent on us,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and so"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "property,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as due from us,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the former as a duty"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the latter as a debt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yavobutu", "text_ar": "يَثْبُتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as the thing lies, or rests, ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yavobutu", "text_ar": "يَثْبُتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) upon the place; the latter phrase importing responsibility: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vabata Ealayohi", "text_ar": "ثَبَتَ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAlN", "text_ar": "مَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also said to mean"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kavura", "text_ar": "كَثُرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "property was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, much in quantity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "amount, upon him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "app."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as a burden imposing upon him responsibility"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And it [likewise] denotes ideal"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstElA='", "text_ar": "استعلا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahumo EalaY~a *anobN", "text_ar": "لَهُمْ عَلَىَّ ذَنْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A crime,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an offence, committed upon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or here, as in many other instances, it may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "against"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "me is imputable to them"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee:) and so in the saying [in the Kur ii. 254 and xvii. 22],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faD~alonaA baEoDahumo EalaY baEoDK", "text_ar": "فَضَّلْنَا بَعْضَهُمْ عَلَى بَعْضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "We have made some of them to have superiority over some"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Es-Subkee, Mughnee, TA.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anota EalaY EayoniY", "text_ar": "اَنْتَ عَلَى عَيْنِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anota EalaY raA^osiY", "text_ar": "اَنْتَ عَلَى رَاْسِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EayonN", "text_ar": "عَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", first quarter.] ―         -b3-  It also denotes concomitance, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEa", "text_ar": "مَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as in the saying [in the Kur ii. 172],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA=taY AlmaAla EalaY Hub~ihi", "text_ar": "وَا=تَى المَالَ عَلَى حُبِّهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And giveth property with"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "notwithstanding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the love of it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee, K;) and so it is said to be used in the phrase, in a trad. respecting the alms of the breaking of the fast [of Ramadán],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY kul~i Hur~K waEabodK SaAEN", "text_ar": "عَلَى كُلِّ حُرٍّ وَعَبْدٍ صَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "With every free man and slave, a sáa"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], because the alms-gift of the breaking of the fast is not incumbent on the slave, but only on his master; (IAth, TA;) and so it is used in the [common] phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^an~aniY raADK", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَنَّنِى رَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "With"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "notwithstanding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "my being pleased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well pleased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "content"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Har p. 13.) ―         -b4-  It also denotes transition, (Mughnee, K,) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eano", "text_ar": "عَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mughnee;) as in the saying (of El-Koheyf El- 'Okeylee, TA),"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A_i*aA raDiyato EalaY~a banuw qu$ayorK\n                      \n                     \n                        laEamoru A@ll~`hi A^aEojabaniY riDaAhaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "When the sons of Kusheyr shall be pleased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well pleased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "content, with me,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or rather, if"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY~a", "text_ar": "عَلَىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here denote transition,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with what will proceed from me,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by the everlasting existence of God, their being pleased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "will induce in me admiration,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pleasure"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Mughnee, K, * TA,) i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ean~iY", "text_ar": "عَنِّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mughnee, TA;) or it may be that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raDiYa", "text_ar": "رَضِىَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is made to imply the meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaTafa", "text_ar": "عَطَفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is trans. by means of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee;) or, as Ks says, it is made to accord with its contr."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saxiTa", "text_ar": "سَخِطَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee, TA,) by its being made trans. by means of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and so in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "fiY layolapK laA naraY bihaA A^aHadFA\n                      \n                     \n                        yaHokiY EalayonaA A_il~aA kawaAkibahaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In a nigh in which we shall not see any one that shall report what will proceed from us, except its stars"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], i. e.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ean~aA", "text_ar": "عَنَّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or it may be said that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaHokiY", "text_ar": "يَحْكِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [here] made to imply the meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yanuim~u", "text_ar": "يَنُِمُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mughnee.) ―         -b5-  It is also used to assign a cause, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as in the saying [in the Kur ii. 181],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walitukab~iruwA A@ll~`ha", "text_ar": "وَلِتُكَبِّرُوا ا@للّٰهَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY maA hadaAkumo", "text_ar": "عَلَى مَا هَدَاكُمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee, K,) meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lihidaAyatihi", "text_ar": "لِهِدَايَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iy~aAkumo", "text_ar": "اـِيَّاكُمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And that ye should magnify God for,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on account of, his rightly directing you"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee;) [and in the same, vi. 90, &c.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA", "text_ar": "لَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asoA^alukumo Ealayohi A^ajorFA", "text_ar": "اَسْاَلُكُمْ عَلَيْهِ اَجْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will not ask of you for it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on account of it, a recompense;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and as in the saying of Rabee'ah Ibn Makroom Ed-Dabbee,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "fadaEawoA nazaAli fakunotu A^aw~ala naAzilK\n                      \n                     \n                        waEalaAma A^arokabuhu A_i*aA lamo A^anozili"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And they called out,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Alight;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "”"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and I was the first of any alighting:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and for what"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wherefore"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "do I ride him if I do not alight"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when called upon to do so? (Ham p. 29. ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaAma", "text_ar": "عَلَامَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is here, as usually, for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY ma", "text_ar": "عَلَى مَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b6-  It is also used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[generally followed by a noun significant of time]; (S, Mughnee, K; *) as in the saying [in the Kur xxviii. 14],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wadaxala A@lomadiynapa", "text_ar": "وَدَخَلَ ا@لْمَدِينَةَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY Hiyni gafolapK", "text_ar": "عَلَى حِينِ غَفْلَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And he entered the city in,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "during, a time of inadvertence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee, K;) and in the saying [in the same ii. 96],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA@t~abaEuwA maA", "text_ar": "وَا@تَّبَعُوا مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tatoluw A@l$~ayaATiynu EalaY muloki sulayomaAna", "text_ar": "تَتْلُو ا@لشَّيَاطِينُ عَلَى مُلْكِ سُلَيْمَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zamani mulki slymAn", "text_ar": "زَمَنِ مُلكِ سليمان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And they followed what the devils related,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "recited, in the time of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "during, the reign of Suleymán"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Solomon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")]; (Mughnee;) and in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAna ka*aA EalaY", "text_ar": "كَانَ كَذَا عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eahodi fulaAnK", "text_ar": "عَهْدِ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eahodihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَهْدِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It was thus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such a thing was, in the time of such a one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) [and in like manner it is used in the saying in the Kur iii. 173,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA kaAna A@ll~`hu liya*ara A@lomuw^ominiyna", "text_ar": "مَا كَانَ ا@للّٰهُ لِيَذَرَ ا@لْمُوْمِنِينَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY maA A^anotumo Ealayohi", "text_ar": "عَلَى مَا اَنْتُمْ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God is not purposing to leave,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "certainly will not leave, the believers in that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "state"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wherein ye are:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY safarK", "text_ar": "عَلَى سَفَرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in ii. 180 &c. of the same, i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or, as we also say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a journey:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in like manner also]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqado", "text_ar": "لَقَدْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sarayotu EalaY AlZ~alaAmi", "text_ar": "سَرَيْتُ عَلَى الظَّلَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in a verse of Aboo-Kebeer El-Hudhalee, means,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY AlZ~alaAmi", "text_ar": "فِى الظَّلَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have journeyed by night in the darkness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fY AlZlAm", "text_ar": "فى الظلام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "holding the place of a noun in the accus. case as a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zarof", "text_ar": "ظَرْف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. an adverbial noun of time or place]; or it may be in the place of a denotative of state, meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA^anaA EalaY AlZ~alaAmi", "text_ar": "وَاَنَا عَلَى الظَّلَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN lahu", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "riding upon the darkness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Ham p. 37:) and you say of one who was desiring to rise and hasten,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotuhu", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^awofaADK", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَوْفَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I found him in a state of haste:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wafoDN", "text_ar": "وَفْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  [It also denotes conformity, accordance, adaptation, or agreement; as in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AiDoribohu EalaY TaboEi h`*aA", "text_ar": "اِضْرِبْهُ عَلَى طَبْعِ هٰذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make thou it, fashion it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mould it, conformably,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "according, to the model, make, fashion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mould, of this;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaboEN", "text_ar": "طَبْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) and in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TubiEa EalaY Al$~aYo'i", "text_ar": "طُبِعَ عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jubila", "text_ar": "جُبِلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuTira", "text_ar": "فُطِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a man)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was created conformably,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with an adaptation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a disposition, to the thing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see 1 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TbE", "text_ar": "طبع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) so too in the phrase in the Kur xxiv. last verse,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qado yaEolamu maA A^anotumo", "text_ar": "قَدْ يَعْلَمُ مَا اَنْتُمْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Certainly He knoweth that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "state of conduct and mind"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to which ye are conforming yourselves;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in many other passages therein: thus also in the saying of Mohammad,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~u mawoluwdK yuwladu EalaY", "text_ar": "كُلُّ مَوْلُودٍ يُولَدُ عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfiTorpi", "text_ar": "الفِطْرةِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Every infant is born in a state of conformity to the natural constitution with which he is created in his mother's womb in relation to the soul;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fTr", "text_ar": "فطر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) and in the prov., mentioned by Meyd,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAsu EalaY diyni Almuluwki", "text_ar": "النَّاسُ عَلَى دِينِ المُلُوكِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The people are in conformity to,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are followers of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "follow, the religion of the kings;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in the phrase, relating to a saying or an opinion,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi A^akovaru AlEulamaA='i", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ اَكْثَرُ العُلَمَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Upon it most of the learned are in agreement;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in which, as in other exs. of the same kind, a verb or a part. n., (in the last, for instance,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mujomiEuwna", "text_ar": "مُجْمِعُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the like,) is understood. ―         -b8-  It also denotes a condition; as in the phrases,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAlaHahu EalaY ka*aA", "text_ar": "صَالَحَهُ عَلَى كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made peace,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "reconciliation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a compromise, with him on the condition of such a thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^ano yafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَنْ يَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on the condition of his doing such a thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b9-  And there are various other usages of this prep. depending upon verbs or part. ns. expressed or obviously understood in connection with them, too numerous to be here collected. Many of these will be found among the explanations of words with which they occur.] ―         -b10-  It is also used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_i*aA A@kotaAluwA EalaY A@ln~aAsi yasotawofuwna", "text_ar": "اـِذَا ا@كْتَالُوا عَلَى ا@لنَّاسِ يَسْتَوْفُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mughnee, K,) in the Kur [lxxxiii. 2], meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mina Aln~aAsi", "text_ar": "مِنَ النَّاسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. Who,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when they take by measure from men, take fully"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S,) or, as in the T,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eani Aln~aAsi", "text_ar": "عَنِ النَّاسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which signifies the same]. (TA.) ―         -b11-  It is also used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Mughnee, K;) as in the saying in the Kur [vii. 103],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^no laA A^aquwla EalaY A@ll~`hi A_il~aA", "text_ar": "عَلَى انْ لَا اَقُولَ عَلَى ا@للّٰهِ اـِلَّا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@loHaq~a", "text_ar": "ا@لْحَقَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee, K, *) meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biA^ano", "text_ar": "بِاَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) [i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That I should not say of God"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "aught"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "save the truth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] and Ubeí read with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "b", "text_ar": "ب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biA^ano", "text_ar": "بِاَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Bd, Mughnee;) like as they say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramayotu EalaY Alqawosi", "text_ar": "رَمَيْتُ عَلَى القَوْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAlqawosi", "text_ar": "بِالقَوْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I shot with the bow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jiy^otu EalaY HaAlK HasanapK", "text_ar": "جِيْتُ عَلَى حَالٍ حَسَنَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biHaAlK HasanapK", "text_ar": "بِحَالٍ حَسَنَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I came in a good condition"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Bd; [in which, and also voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaqiyqN", "text_ar": "حَقِيقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", last sentence, see more;]) and they said also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Airokabo EalaY A@somi A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "اِرْكَبْ عَلَى ا@سْمِ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bisomi A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "بِسْمِ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mount thou in the name of God"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee:) thus [too] it is used in the saying of Aboo-Dhu-eyb,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "yasarN yufiyDu EalaY AlqidaAHi wayaSodaEu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fyD", "text_ar": "فيض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", conj. 4,] meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAlqidaAHi", "text_ar": "بِالقِدَاحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2146}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) [and in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY yadihi", "text_ar": "عَلَى يَدِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "By his hand,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by his means."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b12-  It is also used to denote an emendation, (Mughnee, K,) and a digression, or transition, (Mughnee,) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l`kin~a", "text_ar": "لٰكِنَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN laA yadoxulu Aljan~apa lisuw'i", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ لَا يَدْخُلُ الجَنَّةَ لِسُوءِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaniyEihi", "text_ar": "صَنِيعِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN jahan~amiY~N", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ جَهَنَّمِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^an~ahu", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَنَّهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA y~yoA^asu mino raHompi A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "لَا يّيْاَسُ مِنْ رَحْمةِ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee, K,) meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l`kin~ahu", "text_ar": "لٰكِنَّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one will not enter Paradise, because of the evilness of his deed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conduct,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such a one is hell-doomed; but,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "yet, he will not despair of the mercy of God"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) and thus it is used in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "bikul~K tadaAwayonaA falamo yu$ofa maA binaA\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY A^an~a quroba Ald~aAri xayorN mina AlbuEodi\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY A^an~a quroba Ald~aAri layosa binaAfiEK\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*aA kaAna mano tahowaAhu liyosa bi*iY wad~i"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "With everything we treated,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "have treated, ourselves curatively, and what was in us was not,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has not been, healed; but the nearness of the abode is better than the remoteness; but the nearness of the abode is not profitable when the person whom thou lovest is not endued with affection"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: the poet invalidates by the first"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "his saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falamo yu$ofa", "text_ar": "فَلَمْ يُشْفَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA binaA", "text_ar": "مَا بِنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and then, by the second"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the clause immediately preceding it. (Mughnee.) ―         -b13-  It is also redundant, for the purpose of compensation; as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A_in~a Alkariyma waA^abiyka yaEotamilo\n                      \n                     \n                        A_ino lamo yajido yawomFA EalaY mano yat~akilo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano yat~akilu Ealayohi", "text_ar": "مَنْ يَتَّكِلُ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily the generous, by thy father, will work for himself when he finds not, some day, him upon whom he may rely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "];"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being added before"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano", "text_ar": "مَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the purpose of compensation [for its omission in its proper place]: (Mughnee, K:) Es-Subkee says, it may be redundant, as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A^aHolifu EalaY yamiynK", "text_ar": "لَا اَحْلِفُ عَلَى يَمِينٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA AHlf yamiynFA", "text_ar": "لا احلف يَمِينًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will not swear an oath"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)       -A2-  It is also a noun, having the meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawoq", "text_ar": "فَوْق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "location that is above,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "over"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], this being the case when it is immediately followed by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, Mughnee, K; *) as in the saying (of Muzáhim-El-'Okeylee, describing a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaAp", "text_ar": "قَطَاة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or sand-grouse, and, afterwards, its making a rumbling sound in its inside, from thirst], TA),"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "gadato mino Ealayohi biEoda maA tam~a Zimow^uhaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It went away in the early morning from the location above it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or, as we say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from above it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after that her interval between two comings to water was complete"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Msb, Mughnee, K: [and a similar ex. is cited in the S:]) or, accord. to As, meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Einodihi", "text_ar": "مِنْ عِنْدِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from its vicinage"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and, used in this sense, as a noun, it admits before it no other prep. than"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.)       -A3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayoka", "text_ar": "عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also a verbal noun, used as an incentive: (TA:) you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayoka zayodFA", "text_ar": "عَلَيْكَ زَيْدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bizayodK", "text_ar": "بِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Take thou Zeyd;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "take thou hold of Zeyd:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "keep thou,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cleave thou, to Zeyd:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayoka bika*aA", "text_ar": "عَلَيْكَ بِكَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "keep thou to such a thing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(El-Munáwee, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "b", "text_ar": "ب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) [thus] it is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayoka bAilr~ifoqi", "text_ar": "عَلَيْكَ باِلرِّفْقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Keep thou to gentleness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (El-Jámi' es-Sagheer.) ―         -b2-  And [in like manner] you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY~a zayodFA", "text_ar": "عَلَىَّ زَيْدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bizayodK", "text_ar": "بِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Give thou me,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "present thou to me, Zeyd:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) [or, more commonly,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bring thou to me Zeyd:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY~a bika*aA", "text_ar": "عَلَىَّ بِكَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bring thou to me such a thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Sb", "S", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n30408", "headword_ar": "عُلًى", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaA='N", "text_ar": "عَلَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-  [It is also pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuloyaA", "text_ar": "عُلْيَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", fem. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolaY", "text_ar": "اَعْلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.]"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30422", "headword_ar": "عَلِىٌّ", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "High, elevated,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lofty;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K;) applied to a thing; (K;) [and] so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAlK", "text_ar": "عَالٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) so, too, the former, [and more commonly so,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of rank, condition,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "state; eminent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "noble:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiloyapN", "text_ar": "عِلْيَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a pl. thereof in the latter sense; like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SiboyapN", "text_ar": "صِبْيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabiY~N", "text_ar": "صَبِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; [or, as some hold a word"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2147}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of this form and class to be, a quasi-pl. n.;] as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN mino Eiloyapi Aln~aAsi", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ مِنْ عِلْيَةِ النَّاسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is of the high in rank,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of men"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S;) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiloyapN", "text_ar": "عِلْيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiloYN", "text_ar": "عِلْىٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which latter is of a form proper to quasi-pl. ns. by common consent,] signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "great in respect of estimation, rank,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dignity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of men, thus used in a pl. sense. (K.) ―         -b2-  It signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Strong, robust,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "powerful:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) and hence it is used as a proper name of a man; (K, * TA;) and it may be also from the meaning of highness of rank &c., eminence, or nobility. (TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEaliY~u", "text_ar": "العَلِىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a name of God signifies ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The High:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Most High,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aEolaY", "text_ar": "الاَعْلَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; i. e.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He above whom is nothing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealiy~uwna", "text_ar": "عَلِيُّونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[is also a pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaliY~N", "text_ar": "عَلِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and] signifies Persons"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "alighting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abiding, in the high parts of a country;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this sense opposed to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sufoliy~uwna", "text_ar": "سُفْلِيُّونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": ―         -b5-  and it signifies also Persons"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having opulence,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eminence,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "nobility;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this sense likewise opposed to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sufoliy~uwna", "text_ar": "سُفْلِيُّونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealiy~apN", "text_ar": "عَلِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to a she-camel means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Having strength to bear her burden;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEotaliyapN", "text_ar": "مُعْتَلِيَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaEoliyapN", "text_ar": "مُسْتَعْلِيَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAqapN Haliy~apN Ealiy~apN", "text_ar": "نَاقَةٌ حَلِيَّةٌ عَلِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the former epithet meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pleasing in appearance and pace,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAlyp", "text_ar": "عالية"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[an evident mistranscription for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealiy~apN", "text_ar": "عَلِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "excelling."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b7-  And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN hayYo'N EaliY~N", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ هَيىْءٌ عَلِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is a person of goodly form"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "aspect"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who acts effeminately to women."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n30423", "headword_ar": "عِلِىٌّ", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euluw~N", "text_ar": "عُلُوٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[an inf. n. of 1, q. v.]. (K, TA.) Hence the reading of Ibn-Mes'ood [in the Kur xxvii. 14],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZulomFA waEiliy~FA", "text_ar": "ظُلْمًا وَعِلِيًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "By reason of wrongfulness and self-exaltation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30428", "headword_ar": "عِلِّىٌّ", "root": "Elw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eil~iy~uwna", "text_ar": "عِلِّيُّونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-14", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}